<h2 id="toc2"><span>&#8212;</span></h2>
<div class="showcase">
<h3 id="toc3"><span>BE-Class “Migration” End-of-Consciousness Scenario</span></h3>
<hr />



<div class="scp-image-block block-right" style="width:150px;"><img src="http://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/task-forces/Eta4.png" style="width:150px;" class="enlarge" alt="Eta4.png" />
<div class="scp-image-caption" style="width:150px;">
<p>Eta-4 “Begone Thoth”</p>
</div>
</div>
<p>Did you know that birds have their own gods? Well, “gods” is a term we're not meant to use. We're supposed to use “Apex-tier Pluripotent Entity”, but nobody around is going to enforce that, so why bother?</p>
<p>Anyway, one day, we did something to piss off one of the gods. He got so angry that he came down from his high-and-mighty throne in who-knows-where and tried to wipe the human population off the face of the Earth by giving them bird minds. It worked, and now I think we're all screwed.</p>
<p>Who are we? We're Mobile Task Force Eta-4, otherwise known as “Begone Thoth”. I swear to Medila, I'm going to track down and peck whoever decided on that name&#8230; But, I digress. It's our job to uphold the mission of the Old Foundation. Seventy-five birds against seven billion humans, a god, and Medila-knows how many anomalies (some of them from Thoth himself). The odds are bleak, I know. But we've got brains, determination, and a whole lot of bird-power. If we pull this off right, we can stop this apocalypse.</p>
<div style="text-align: right;">
<p>Medila help us all.</p>
<hr />
<p>&#8212;Dr. Frederick Hoygull, PhD<br />
<em>Avian Division Head</em></p>
</div>
</div>
